<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/943739-i-m-thinking-of-this-book-in-the-context">I&#39;m thinking of this book in the context of the recent US Presidential election: voters making a choice between the candidates, based on uncertainty / probabilities of course. So many people viewed both candidates as a loss; or one as a definite loss of some unknown magnitude, and the other as a possible gain of unknown magnitude. Can someone help me sort out this analysis, in light of this book?</a>
</div>
